axon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "human", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.6510005593299866, "span": {"begin": 752, "end": 757}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:915"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "anti-CD3", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9557373523712158, "span": {"begin": 770, "end": 778}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:940"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD28", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9737951755523682, "span": {"begin": 779, "end": 783}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "PBMC", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8978772759437561, "span": {"begin": 803, "end": 807}}, {"id": ["mesh:D016559"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "FK506", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9991587400436401, "span": {"begin": 833, "end": 838}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:55379"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CsA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9970763921737671, "span": {"begin": 842, "end": 845}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:959"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "IgM", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9865873456001282, "span": {"begin": 860, "end": 863}}, {"id": ["mesh:D016559"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "FK506", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9985358715057373, "span": {"begin": 962, "end": 967}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:55379"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CsA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.7801958918571472, "span": {"begin": 1016, "end": 1019}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10116"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Rats", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9746301770210266, "span": {"begin": 1044, "end": 1048}}, {"id": ["mesh:D016559"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "FK506", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9989383816719055, "span": {"begin": 1067, "end": 1072}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:9365"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "KLH", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9910973310470581, "span": {"begin": 1109, "end": 1112}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:51409"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "anti-KLH IgM", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9900056719779968, "span": {"begin": 1142, "end": 1154}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:8857"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "IgG", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9929705262184143, "span": {"begin": 1159, "end": 1162}}, {"id": ["CL:0000084"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "T cell", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.6050602793693542, "span": {"begin": 1355, "end": 1361}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "KEs", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.6970370411872864, "span": {"begin": 1452, "end": 1455}}], "text": "Empirical support for the suppression of IL-4 production leads to impairment, and the T cell dependent antibody response is strong.  Rationale  In CD3/PMA activated human T cells, FK506 suppressed the production of IL-2, IL-4, and IFN-&gamma; at concentrations of 1.2 to 12.5 nM and inhibited the expression of IL-2, IL-4, and IFN-&gamma; mRNA at concentrations of 10 nM (Dumont, et al. 1998).  After 9-day culture of B cells and non-pre-activated T cell stimulation with FK506 or CsA, the levels of IgM and IgG in the culture supernatant were reduced. The FK506 levels were 0.3 and 1.0 ng/mL (0.37 and 1.24 nM) and the CsA levels were 50 and 100 ng/mL (41 and 83 nM) (Heidt, et al. 2010).  After a 4-day culture of SKW6.4 IL-6-dependent IgM-secreting human B cells and anti-CD3/CD28 stimulation of the PBMC culture supernatant with FK506 or CsA, the level of IgM in the culture supernatant was reduced at concentrations of 0.01 to 100 ng/mL (0.01 to 124 nM) of FK506 and &nbsp;0.1 to 1000 ng/mL (0.08 to 832 nM) of CsA (Sakuma, et al. 2001).  Rats were treated with FK506 for over 4 weeks and immunized with KLH. The serum concentrations of anti-KLH IgM and IgG were reduced at a dose of 3 mg/kg/day (Ulrich, et al. 2004).  In vitro suppression of T cell derived cytokines and T cell dependent antibody production or antibody production after polyclonal T cell stimulation showed similar dose responses to CNIs. Time gaps were found between these two KEs, which showed earlier onset of cytokine production and delayed onset of antibody production.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:24:18 +0000 2026"}